  Our Leadership


  Commitment, discipline, and our extensive experience working together in the healthcare real estate industry creates a strong foundation for Care Capital Properties.













    Focused Expertise, Committed to Growth  

As leaders, we share a passion for the post-acute healthcare real estate market, our assets, and the customers we serve. We are committed to thoughtfully expanding our business and providing opportunities for our team and customers to grow. 
Our knowledgeable, independent board of directors is composed of recognized leaders in real estate, finance, and healthcare. Our team has an accomplished record of successfully identifying and executing attractive acquisition opportunities across the healthcare real estate spectrum. Our expertise in raising capital and prudently managing our assets and balance sheet positions us to lead the consolidation of this dynamic and fragmented industry.









Executive Leadership Team
Board of Directors




Executive Leadership Team
As a leadership team, we are passionate and knowledgeable about our industry, our assets, and our customers.







 Raymond J. Lewis Chief Executive Officer                  
Mr. Lewis has been our Chief Executive Officer since our spin-off from Ventas, Inc. in 2015. Previously, Mr. Lewis served as President of Ventas from 2010 to 2015; as Executive Vice President and Chief Investment Officer of Ventas from 2006 to 2010; and as Senior Vice President and Chief Investment Officer of Ventas from 2002 to 2006. 


View Profile 



 Kristen M. Benson Executive Vice President, General Counsel, and Corporate Secretary                  
Ms. Benson has been our Executive Vice President, General Counsel, and Corporate Secretary since our spin-off from Ventas, Inc. in 2015. Previously, Ms. Benson served as Senior Vice President, Associate General Counsel, and Corporate Secretary of Ventas from 2014 to 2015; as Vice President, Associate General Counsel, and Corporate Secretary of Ventas from 2012 to 2014; as Vice President and Senior Securities Counsel of Ventas from 2007 to 2012; and as Senior Securities Counsel of Ventas from 2004 to 2007.


View Profile 



 Timothy A. Doman Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer                  
Mr. Doman has been our Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer since our spin-off from Ventas, Inc. in 2015.  Previously, Mr. Doman served as Senior Vice President and Chief Portfolio Officer of Ventas from 2012 to 2015; as Senior Vice President, Asset Management of Ventas from 2007 to 2012; and as Vice President, Asset Management of Ventas from 2002 to 2007.


View Profile 



 Lori B. Wittman Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer                  
Ms. Wittman has been our Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer since our spin-off from Ventas, Inc. in 2015. Previously, Ms. Wittman served as Senior Vice President, Capital Markets and Investor Relations of Ventas from 2013 to 2015 and as Vice President, Capital Markets and Investor Relations of Ventas from 2011 to 2013. 


View Profile 








Board of Directors
Care Capital Properties benefits from the expertise and guidance of a strong, independent board. Our directors, who are recognized leaders in the real estate, finance and healthcare industries, provide valuable wisdom and oversight.
Our board has five standing committees: Audit and Compliance Committee (responsible for independent audits and management controls), Nominating and Governance Committee (responsible for nominating director candidates and corporate governance matters), Compensation Committee (responsible for establishing financial remuneration and benefits for our executive officers and directors), Investment Committee (responsible for reviewing our investment and divestiture transactions), and Executive Committee (responsible for directing selected business affairs during intervals between general board meetings).







Douglas Crocker II Chairman of the Board          
  Compensation Committee, Investment Committee (Chair), and Executive Committee (Chair)
 
Mr. Crocker currently serves as Managing Partner of DC Partners LLC, a firm that invests in and develops apartment properties, where he previously served as principal from 2003 to 2006. From 2006 to 2014, Mr. Crocker was the Chairman and Chief Investment Officer of Pearlmark Multifamily Partners, L.L.C., a commercial real estate firm.


View Profile 



John S. Gates, Jr. Director          
  Compensation Committee (Chair) and Nominating and Governance Committee
 
Mr. Gates has been Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of PortaeCo, LLC, a private investment company, since 2006.  Mr. Gates co-founded CenterPoint Properties Trust (NYSE: CNT) (“CenterPoint”), the United States’ first publicly traded industrial REIT, in 1984 and served as its Co-Chairman and Chief Executive Officer for the next 22 years. 


View Profile 



Ronald G. Geary Director          
  Audit and Compliance Committee (Chair) and Investment Committee
 
Mr. Geary has been President of Ellis Park Race Course, Inc., a thoroughbred racetrack in Henderson, Kentucky since 2006. He previously served as President of Res-Care, Inc. (formerly NASDAQ: RSCR), a provider of residential training and support services for persons with developmental disabilities.


View Profile 



