What is Care Capital Properties' stock symbol?

Care Capital Properties trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "CCP."



How often does Care Capital Properties pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for Care Capital Properties?

Care Capital Properties declared a quarterly dividend on Friday, May 19th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 9th will be given a dividend of $0.57 per share on Friday, June 30th. This represents a $2.28 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 9.15%. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, June 7th.  View Care Capital Properties' Dividend History.



How were Care Capital Properties' earnings last quarter?

Care Capital Properties, Inc. (NYSE:CCP) released its earnings results on Tuesday, May, 9th. The company reported $0.68 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.42 by $0.26. The company earned $82.80 million during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $83.32 million. Care Capital Properties had a return on equity of 13.48% and a net margin of 45.61%. The business's quarterly revenue was down 2.0% on a year-over-year basis.  View Care Capital Properties' Earnings History.



When will Care Capital Properties make its next earnings announcement?

Care Capital Properties is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Wednesday, August, 9th 2017. View Earnings Estimates for Care Capital Properties.



Where is Care Capital Properties' stock going? Where will Care Capital Properties' stock price be in 2017?

4 analysts have issued 12 month price objectives for Care Capital Properties' stock. Their forecasts range from $20.00 to $33.00. On average, they expect Care Capital Properties' share price to reach $26.00 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for Care Capital Properties.



Who are some of Care Capital Properties' key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to Care Capital Properties include Medical Properties Trust (MPW), Healthcare Realty Trust Incorporated (HR), National Health Investors (NHI), Physicians Realty Trust (DOC), LTC Properties (LTC), Assura PLC (AGR), Primary Health Properties PLC (PHP), MedEquities Realty Trust (MRT), Community Healthcare Trust Incorporated (CHCT), Aviv REIT (AVIV), CareTrust REIT (CTRE), Global Medical REIT (GMRE) and Sabra Healthcare REIT (SBRA).



Who are Care Capital Properties' key executives?

Care Capital Properties' management team includes the folowing people: Raymond J. Lewis, Chief Executive Officer, DirectorLori B. Wittman, Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice PresidentTimothy A. Doman, Chief Operating Officer, Executive Vice PresidentKristen Michelle Benson, Executive Vice President, General Counsel, Corporate SecretaryDouglas Crocker II, Non-Executive Independent Chairman of the BoardJohn S. Gates Jr., Independent DirectorRonald G. Geary, Independent DirectorJeffrey A. Malehorn, Independent DirectorDale Anne Reiss, Independent Director



Who owns Care Capital Properties stock?

Care Capital Properties' stock is owned by many different of retail and institutional investors. Top institutional investors include APG Asset Management US Inc. (1.56%), Longfellow Investment Management Co. LLC (0.52%), Chicago Capital Management LLC (0.51%), Aperio Group LLC (0.38%), Gateway Investment Advisers LLC (0.22%) and Strs Ohio (0.16%). Company insiders that own Care Capital Properties stock include Douglas Crocker II, Jeffrey A Malehorn, John L Workman, John S Gates Jr and Raymond J Lewis. View Institutional Ownership Trends for Care Capital Properties.



Who sold Care Capital Properties stock? Who is selling Care Capital Properties stock?

Care Capital Properties' stock was sold by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including APG Asset Management US Inc., Denali Advisors LLC, Pensionfund DSM Netherlands, Municipal Employees Retirement System of Michigan, Schnieders Capital Management LLC, Public Employees Retirement Association of Colorado, Oxbow Advisors LLC and Creative Planning.  View Insider Buying and Selling for Care Capital Properties.



Who bought Care Capital Properties stock? Who is buying Care Capital Properties stock?

Care Capital Properties' stock was acquired by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Longfellow Investment Management Co. LLC, Chicago Capital Management LLC, Aperio Group LLC, Acadian Asset Management LLC, State of Alaska Department of Revenue, Virtu Financial LLC, Forsta AP Fonden and ING Groep NV. Company insiders that have bought Care Capital Properties stock in the last two years include Douglas Crocker II, Jeffrey A Malehorn, John L Workman, John S Gates Jr and Raymond J Lewis. View Insider Buying and Selling for Care Capital Properties.



How do I buy Care Capital Properties stock? 

Shares of Care Capital Properties can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is Care Capital Properties' stock price today?

One share of Care Capital Properties stock can currently be purchased for approximately $24.93.


