Care Capital Properties, Inc. Key Developments

Faruqi & Faruqi, LLP Announces Filing of Class Action Lawsuit against Care Capital Properties, Inc
Jul 20 17
Faruqi & Faruqi, LLP has filed a class action lawsuit in the United States District Court for the District of Delaware, case no. 1:17-cv-00859, on behalf of shareholders of Care Capital Properties, Inc., who have been harmed by Care Capital's and its board of directors' alleged violations of Sections 14(a) and 20(a) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 in connection with the proposed sale of the company to Sabra Health Care REIT, Inc. On May 7, 2017, the company announced it had entered into an Agreement and Plan of Merger under which each outstanding share of Care Capital common stock will be exchanged for 1.123 common shares of Sabra for an implied value of $29.96 per share based on Sabra's closing price on May 5, 2017. The shareholder vote on the Proposed Transaction is expected to occur on August 15, 2017. The complaint alleges that the Form S-4 Registration Statement filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission on June 12, 2017 to solicit votes in favor of the Proposed Transaction violates Sections 14(a) and 20(a) of the Exchange Act because it provides materially incomplete and misleading information about the company and the Proposed Transaction, including material information concerning the company's financial projections and analyses, on which the Board relied to recommend the Proposed Transaction as fair to Care Capital shareholders.


Care Capital Properties, Inc. Presents at 10th Annual Investment and M&A Opportunities in Healthcare, Jun-08-2017 09:15 AM
Jun 6 17
Care Capital Properties, Inc. Presents at 10th Annual Investment and M&A Opportunities in Healthcare, Jun-08-2017 09:15 AM. Venue: Loews Vanderbilt Hotel, 2100 West End Ave, Nashville, TN 37203, United States. Speakers: Adam Zeiger, Senior Investment Officer.


Care Capital Properties, Inc. Presents at NAREIT's REITWeek Investor Forum, Jun-06-2017
Jun 6 17
Care Capital Properties, Inc. Presents at NAREIT's REITWeek Investor Forum, Jun-06-2017 . Venue: The New York Hilton Midtown, New York, New York, United States.


